  Finance(
    title:
        'If You Invested \$10,000 In Equinix Stock 10 Years Ago, How Much Would You Have Now?',
    body:
        'Benzinga and Yahoo Finance LLC may earn commission or revenue on some items through the links below.\n\nEquinix (NASDAQ:EQIX) is the world\'s digital infrastructure company. It interconnects industry-leading organizations in finance, manufacturing, retail, transportation, government, health care and education in a digital-first world.\n\nIt is set to report its Q4 2024 earnings on Feb. 12, 2025. Wall Street analysts expect the company to post revenues of \$2.26 billion, up from \$2.11 billion in the previous year.\n\nDon\'t Miss:\n\nCommercial real estate has historically outperformed the stock market, and this platform allows individuals to invest in commercial real estate with as little as \$5,000 offering a 12% target yield with a bonus 1% return boost today!\n\nThis Jeff Bezos-backed startup will allow you to become a landlord in just 10 minutes, and you only need \$100.\n\nIf You Bought Equinix Stock 10 Years Ago\nThe company\'s stock traded at approximately \$221.97 per share 10 years ago. If you had invested \$10,000, you could have bought roughly 45 shares. Currently, shares trade at \$901.15, meaning your investment\'s value could have grown to \$40,598 from stock price appreciation alone. However, Equinix also paid dividends during these 10 years.\n\nEquinix\'s dividend yield is currently 1.89%. Over the last 10 years, it has paid about \$117.72 in dividends per share, which means you could have made \$5,303 from dividends alone.\n\nSumming up \$40,598 and \$5,303, we end up with the final value of your investment, which is \$45,901. This is how much you could have made if you had invested \$10,000 in Equinix stock 10 years ago. This means a total return of 359.01%. In comparison, S&P 500 total return for the same period is 233.31%.\n\nTrending: During market downturns, investors are learning that unlike equities, these high-yield real estate notes that pay 7.5% – 9% are protected by resilient assets, buffering against losses.\n\nWhat Could The Next 10 Years Bring?\nEquinix has a consensus rating of "Buy" and a price target of \$882.07 based on the ratings of 31 analysts. The price target implies more than 2% potential downside from the current stock price.\n\nOn Oct. 30, the company announced its Q3 2024 earnings, posting an AFFO of \$9.05, beating the consensus estimate of \$8.70 and revenues of \$2.20 billion, matching expectations, as reported by Benzinga.\n\n“Our 87th consecutive quarter of revenue growth was also a record-breaking one for gross bookings, with strong results across our three regions. This performance is a testament to the trust our customers place in Equinix and the value they realize in partnering strategically with us. We see continued robust demand for AI-enabling digital infrastructure from a highly diverse set of customers of varying sizes, industries and regions," said Adaire Fox-Martin, CEO and President of Equinix.\n\nSee Also: Wondering if your investments can get you to a \$5,000,000 nest egg? Speak to a financial advisor today. SmartAsset’s free tool matches you up with up to three vetted financial advisors who serve your area, and you can interview your advisor matches at no cost to decide which one is right for you.\n\nGiven the expected downside potential, growth-focused investors may not find Equinix stock attractive. Conversely, the stock can be a good option for income-focused investors, who can benefit from the company\'s solid dividend yield of 1.89% and consistent hikes. Equinix has raised its dividend consecutively for the last eight years.\n\nCheck out this article by Benzinga for three more stocks offering high dividend yields.\n\nLooking For Higher-Yield Opportunities In A Shifting Market?\nThe changing interest rate environment has created an incredible opportunity for income-seeking investors to earn massive yields, but not through dividend stocks... Certain private market real estate investments are giving retail investors the opportunity to capitalize on these high-yield opportunities and Benzinga has identified some of the most attractive options for you to consider.\n\nFor instance, the Ascent Income Fund from EquityMultiple targets stable income from senior commercial real estate debt positions and has a historical distribution yield of 12.1% backed by real assets. With payment priority and flexible liquidity options, the Ascent Income Fund is a cornerstone investment vehicle for income-focused investors. First-time investors with EquityMultiple can now invest in the Ascent Income Fund with a reduced minimum of just \$5,000. Benzinga Readers: Earn a 1% return boost on your first EquityMultiple investment when you sign up here (accredited investors only).',
